check.check-content:
Ask the application representative to review web pages, and determine if the application sets the character set.
Perl After the last header look for print "Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8\n\n";
PHP. Look for the header() function before any content is generated header('Content-type: text/html; charset=utf-8');
Java Servlets. Look for the setContentType method on the ServletResponse object Objectname.setContentType ("text/html;charset=utf-8");
JSP. Look for a page directives <%@ page contentType="text/html; charset=UTF-8" %>
ASP Look for Response.charset <%Response.charset="utf-8"%>
ASP.Net Look for Response.ContentEncoding Response.ContentEncoding = Encoding.UTF8;
1) If the application representative cannot demonstrate the above, it is a finding.
